<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-01-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-01-19"><hi rend="italic">January 19,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: By direction of the Marquis of Salisbury,
                            I have the honor to inquire whether passengers leaving Spain for Cuba
                            and Porto Rico are required to provide themselves with passports.</p>
                        <p>I shall be greatly obliged if you will kindly furnish me with this
                            information in order that I may reply to the telegraphic inquiry from
                            Lord Salisbury.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>